Randy,

It was great catching up at dinner last night. As I mentioned, we are actively looking to add
additional payment gateways to our platform that will enable us to support a wider array of
merchants and increase our overall revenue. Almost all gateways can be categorized as either very
large (First Data, Chase Paymentech, TSYS, Global, Elavon, Vantiv) or smaller, more niche
gateways.

Our preference is always to work with the large gateways first as we are confident in their long-
term stability and support resources. CardConnect is an exception to this rule. As you know, they
were recently acquired by a very large payments company (First Data) and we are pursuing an
integration to them despite originating as a “smaller gateway”. Still, we have a number of mutual
customers with CardConnect so the integration does make sense.

There are a few more “niche” gateways that we will be integrating with this year and next in order
to support specialized software applications. Specifically, we have allocated resources for
integrations with the following gateways:

•	Payrix (fka Retriever Payment Systems)
•	Secure Net
•	USAePay

I have included the contact information for the appropriate people at each organization on this
email. Angela Tesman from my team will follow-up with each of them to begin the integration
process. Please let me know if you have any questions. Thank you.

Jared

Randy,

It was great catching up at dinner last night. As I mentioned, we are actively looking to add
additional payment gateways to our platform that will enable us to support a wider array of
merchants and increase our overall revenue. Almost all gateways can be categorized as either very
large (First Data, Chase Paymentech, TSYS, Global, Elavon, Vantiv) or smaller, more niche
gateways.

Our preference is always to work with the large gateways first as we are confident in their long-
term stability and support resources. CardConnect is an exception to this rule. As you know, they
were recently acquired by a very large payments company (First Data) and we are pursuing an
integration to them despite originating as a “smaller gateway”. Still, we have a number of mutual
customers with CardConnect so the integration does make sense.

There are a few more “niche” gateways that we will be integrating with this year and next in order
to support specialized software applications. Specifically, we have allocated resources for
integrations with the following gateways:

•	Payrix (fka Retriever Payment Systems)
•	Secure Net
•	USAePay

I have included the contact information for the appropriate people at each organization on this
email. Angela Tesman from my team will follow-up with each of them to begin the integration
process. Please let me know if you have any questions. Thank you.

Jared
